<title>UK: UK Labour's Blair sees EMU hard to join in 1999.</title>
<headline>UK Labour's Blair sees EMU hard to join in 1999.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Tony Blair, leader of Britain's main opposition Labour Party, said on Tuesday there would be &quot;obvious and formidable difficulties&quot; in the way of joining the European Union planned single cuurency when it was launched in 1999.</p>
<p>Speaking at a campaign news conference , Blair said Labour's position of keeping its options open about the merits of signing up for economic and monetary union was in Britain's best interest.</p>
<p>Labour, like the ruling Conservatives, has pledged to submit any future decision by a Labour government to join EMU to a referendum.</p>
